doc.after: Turtles are reptiles characterised by a special bony or cartilaginous shell developed from their ribs that acts as a shield The earliest known turtles date from 157 million years ago Turtles are ectotherms they vary their internal temperature according to the ambient environment commonly known as cold bloodedness However leatherback sea turtles have noticeably higher body temperature than surrounding water because of their high metabolic rate Though turtles live in and around water they breathe air and lay eggs on land
